<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Is Gemini Search more accurate than ChatGPT Search?</strong></p>
<p>For factual, time-sensitive queries, yes. Gemini scored 72.1% on the SimpleQA verified accuracy benchmark compared to 34.9% for ChatGPT. Gemini's direct access to Google's search index gives it fresher and more accurate real-time data. For creative or analytical queries, ChatGPT produces more structured and useful responses.</p>
<p><strong>Does ChatGPT Search send more traffic to websites than Gemini?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. ChatGPT generates 87.4% of all AI referral traffic to websites. It produces inline citations that users click. Visitors from ChatGPT convert at twice the rate of traditional search visitors. Gemini drives less referral traffic because its answers are more self-contained within the Google ecosystem.</p>
<p><strong>Can I optimize my content for both Gemini and ChatGPT Search?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. The core optimization strategies overlap. Write well-structured content with specific statistics, implement schema markup, maintain freshness, and build authority across multiple platforms. Our <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization guide</a> covers the unified approach in detail.</p>
<p><strong>Which AI search engine is growing faster?</strong></p>
<p>Gemini is growing faster from a smaller base. Its AI chatbot app market share jumped from 14.7% to 25.2% in one year. ChatGPT's share declined from 69.1% to 45.3% in the app market during the same period. Both platforms are growing in total users. The market is expanding overall.</p>
<p><strong>How does Gemini Search relate to Google AI Overviews?</strong></p>
<p>Gemini's technology powers Google AI Overviews. AI Overviews appear on roughly 25% of Google searches. Optimizing for Gemini Search and optimizing for <a href="/glossary/ai-overviews/">AI Overviews</a> are effectively the same task. Content that Gemini cites in its search responses is the same content Google surfaces in AI Overviews.</p>
<p><strong>Should I block or allow AI crawlers from these platforms?</strong></p>
<p>Allow them. Blocking GPTBot (ChatGPT) or Google-Extended (Gemini) prevents your content from appearing in AI search results. Unless you have a specific licensing reason to block AI access, keeping crawlers enabled maximizes your visibility. Read our <a href="/blog/ai-crawlers-guide/">AI crawlers guide</a> for specific configuration steps.</p>
<p>AI search is not one platform. It is two major platforms with different retrieval methods, different citation models, and different user bases. The businesses that win in 2026 are the ones visible on both Gemini Search and ChatGPT Search, not just one.</p>
